<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-818] Canopy Emits Too Many Trivial Clusters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-818</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Users of Canopy clustering report that the single reducer used in the mapreduce version often takes dispropportately long to process the results of multiple mappers. This patch introduces a new Canopy CLI argument, &lt;del&gt;cf (&lt;/del&gt;-clusterFilter), which if present establishes a lower bound on the numPoints of canopies output from the algorithm. The default value for this filter is 0, and all canopies are output. Setting -cf 1 would eliminate any canopies which contain only 1 point from subsequent processing steps.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
